  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n98de05c4a747a54fa2d6991d76d81f3ab1526cba\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nanvil\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI think `eth_feeHistory` returns one too many `baseFeePerGas` and `gasUsedRatio` elements. The example below is asking for 1 block of history, and it should return 2 base fee per gas element and 1 gas used ratio element, but returns 3 and 2.\r\n\r\n```\r\ncurl --verbose -X POST -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\r\n  --data '{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"eth_feeHistory\", \"params\": [\"0x1\", \"latest\", []], \"id\": 1}' http://127.0.0.1:8545\r\n\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":{\r\n  \"baseFeePerGas\":[\"0x1318c484\",\"0x10da0bbd\",\"0xedee35e\"],\r\n  \"gasUsedRatio\":[0.029765733333333332,0.029761433333333333],\r\n  \"oldestBlock\":\"0xa\",\"reward\":[]}}‚èé\r\n```\r\n",
